title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: Hello. Got this board here that had been messed on another shop. Missing PM_SLP_S5_L. There were some missing components and some bad resistors underneath CPU and R1905 was missing which I replaced. I get stable 8.56V on PPBUS and stable 3v3_S5 power rail but no PM_SLP_S5_L. Which signals exactly are needed to create it?

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message:
PM_SLP_S5_L will stay low, until board exit from S5 state.
Do you get 3V3_SUS?

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse at PM_PWRBTN_L (at same time).

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: Yes it drops when triggering SMC_ONOFF_L

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: Now check if any PM_SLP_Sx_L reacts at the same time.

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: No, I get no pulses on ant PM_SLP when triggering SMC_ONOFF

title: 820-3437 Missing PM_SLP_S5_L
message: They probably killed the CPU in other service; if wasn't dead already.
